[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating security manager in native executable**\n\nI'm thinking about whether I can allow setSecurityManager in a native executable. It seems I need to pass `-Djava.security.manager=allow` as runtime arguments for native tests too. But does Native Image actually support SecurityManager? If I'm considering JDK 21, it feels like setSecurityManager might be unsupported. I wonder if the native runtime relies on substrate, which could mean that the security manager isn't supported at all. It's quite tricky!\n\n**Considering method retrieval**\n\nI'm thinking about the `getMethods` function and whether it returns only reachable methods without metadata. It seems like there could be complications since tests involve many inner classes that might not be configured properly. If the user-code-filter excludes test classes, it could lead to failures. To maintain a native pass, I’m wondering if targeting an entity could be a Spring class with a public static finder might be the way to go.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_02a51bb882244cd70169f5b5ebd7a8819388ca8e8e1cf9214d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9bYBzZkLAyi4tg10cBSfwbs1_wz8HxrjwqZvr-ixiZsSi2ffmMjvxNDwky7A51l1cjsVmqy7M5860XJnSLQx0tUWurLiOlZiVYeHseHML1uhbO9uDoNc2NToGsoB5O5NtvnQvWeSjwOEBTlvPQuzByW_RnGzkD1jkYtLtLRlkUuzV2XfeNEsxukHPUD8DWrTk_KNu8nyNgxpIbUirMDDzaarEROiHps2l_7fwZIzkmidBksqpTLBlwMQCwyQBmzXQ3ladgZtQl_actnjf1FWXiEY-MMacVh3AGRETFFq24D7yROLkykROJJ7zcNWwkSr4jw6hcdNkJvBa2Y2IHfKnSvYu-5UoOcSJSCv0QpRWrMaj8itV_kchXlFQOgrBms6JDHmEFg1p0T2BipDRIOb7UjHA1S4Hqo7bJ6FIgV-qMi52B-Xuz1PR4JmaycQ1L9dt7TFeygzIYtI63pp30rZsre03TneuHwpndXUsqglPML-ltwSYbU5owURZV5tCc9gSSzd7w7Z59nBKwwfMffyEiMV1Gh1zZcc-CcbjSacEfmUkO9Jq7pzhAL4TS7SlrL95qfrpC67tSnq7tAf3bsqDZQ48Edcco5brBv1x8CvCAIAX9LcJugWMFgjgL3UyFSvqyDOXIBDIxiWKvRH7wi4NVaJ6shdl--spqgy8-Te6sJt3PyVHDlIinpVCDdEUa6aJb_9D2LXA5Nhyq2lkrhm8lJLFwyGgBirsj4OpiVFWtXqf