[assistant] Implemented a stronger targeted coverage test for `IdToEntityConverter`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Added:
[assistant] - `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_core/IdToEntityConverterTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] What changed:
[assistant] - Replaced the previous `SecurityManager` approach, since modern JDKs no longer reliably throw from `Class#getDeclaredMethods()` for this path.
[assistant] - The new test installs a temporary bytecode transformer for `org.springframework.core.convert.support.IdToEntityConverter`.
[assistant] - The transformer redirects the `Class#getDeclaredMethods()` call inside `getFinder(...)` to a test helper that throws `SecurityException`.
[assistant] - This forces Spring’s existing fallback branch to execute:
[assistant]   - `entityClass.getMethods()`
[assistant] - The test then verifies that conversion still succeeds via a public static finder method:
[assistant]   - `findSecureLookupEntity(Long)`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Native Image handling:
[assistant] - The transformer uses dynamic instrumentation, so unsupported dynamic loading errors are validated with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(...)`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Also:
[assistant] - Reverted the earlier `build.gradle` SecurityManager JVM arg change; only the dedicated test file remains modified.
[assistant] - Per instruction, I did not compile or run tests.
